messages.text: Hey, is this Jess Daniels?
Yeah. Who’s this?
My name’s Griffin Blake. Justin Jones gave me your number.
Justin did that? Why?
He thought we’d hit it off.
Idk, this is kinda weird, Griffin…
And honestly, I’m kinda crushin on someone else.
Justin said you’d say that.
Haha, well Justin knows me really well.
He’s my best friend.
Ha—he told me that.
And he also told me that you like Italian food.
I do too.
So…? That doesn’t mean that we’d be a good couple.
Ha—that’s harsh.
How about that author, Madeleine L’Engle? Justin said you like her.
OMG, I’m OBSESSED with her.
A Wrinkle in Time is my favorite book EVER.
I’ve read it every year since fourth grade…and every year, it gives me something new.
Yeah, I like books too—but I usually only read them once.
My favorite author’s Mark Twain.
Ugh, what’s with boys and Mark Twain? I hate those “school” authors.
Wait—hear me out. When I read Huck Finn in school it totally sucked.
We over-analyzed every single word.
But then I read A Connecticut Yankee in King Arthur’s Court—
And that shit was HILARIOUS.
Hmm, maybe I’ll try it.
Have you read A Wrinkle in Time?
Yeah—a long time ago. But I remember liking it.
You just “liked it”?? Sounds like you weren’t reading it carefully.
Slow your roll there, Teach.
If you want me to read it again, I will.
You’d do that for me? You don’t even know me.
I don’t, but I know Justin. And I think he’s a great guy.
He IS a great guy, isn’t he?
The best. That’s why I trust him to set me up with someone amazing.
Griffin…
I still don’t know you.
But we can GET to know each other.
Please? Let’s take this slow.
Okay.
one minute later
Justin, what the HELL?!
Hello to you too, darling Jess.
Don’t “darling Jess” me!
How could you set me up with someone WITHOUT telling me?!
I don’t see what the big deal is.
I was just trying to do a nice thing for a friend…
It’s NOT a nice thing. You didn’t warn me!
Look, Jess—Griffin’s a great guy.
I thought he’d treat you better than all those douchebags you usually date.
Whoa, back up.
Who are YOU to say which guys are right for me?
Um, I think I know you pretty well. Don’t I?
Justin, you’re my best friend…
But don’t you see that this is kind of  a jerk thing to do?
No—I’m just trying to help!
I don’t need it. I’m perfectly capable of helping myself.
I know. I’m sorry.
Jess, it’s just—I think that you’re the most amazing girl in the world.
And I want you to be with someone who sees that.
Who treats you that way.
Ugh, that was really sweet.
I wish I could keep hating you right now…
Does that mean I’m forgiven?
Haha please! You won’t get off that easily. 😛
two minutes later
Ugh, Mandy…Justin set me up with someone.
WHAT?! Oh no…
I know. It sucks so much that I like him.
He obviously doesn’t feel the same way if he’s setting me up with people.
Aw, Jess, don’t say that.
It’s the truth though. It’s better if I just face it.
I guess. I mean, what’s so great about Justin anyway?
You’re always complaining about him.
I am, but that’s because he doesn’t want to date me.
Justin’s the best guy I know.
He always tries to look out for me…
And still supports me no matter what I choose.
So, kinda like me? LOL
Haha, yeah. But Justin’s really hot.
ROTFL. Fair assessment.
Hey—wanna go to Starbucks?
I do, but I have to stay home to sign for an important package for my mom.
Sucks. She’s working again?
Yeah. But it’s okay. I guess it gives me time to read some Mark Twain.
What?! We hate those “school” authors.
I know, but Justin’s friend, Griffin, really likes Twain.
And since Griffin’s reading A Wrinkle in Time, I feel like I should read his favorite book too.
Who knows? If I can’t have Justin, maybe Griffin will be the next best thing.
Idk, Jess…Don’t you think this could get confusing?
What do you mean?
This Griffin guy—have you actually met him?
No…he texted me for the first time today.
He said we could take it slow.
I thought it was sweet.
It is, but I still think this is going to be a problem.
Why?!
Because he’s Justin’s friend, so he’s probably pretty similar to him.
Okay, so…?
So you still like Justin.
AND you can’t see this guy’s face.
You’re totally going to superimpose your feelings for Justin on Griffin.
Am not!
Mark my words, Jess—
This is going to be a mistake.
the next day
OMG, A Wrinkle in Time was AMAZING!!!
Haha, I told you!
I stayed up all night reading it.
I want to live in Uriel SO bad.
OMG me too.
I feel like I’d get along with the creatures there.
Ha, you would! Listen, I know this is stupid—
But I kept imagining you as Meg.
Haha, I don’t look anything like her.
What DO you look like?
I don’t know. I’m average.
Want me to send a selfie?
No. This may seem cheesy and romantic—
But I want to see you for the first time in person, when we finally meet.
How would you describe yourself?
Well, I’m 5’6.” And I have short black hair and brown eyes.
My dad’s white so my skin’s pretty light…
But otherwise, I don’t know if I look anything like him.
Wait—why?
He wasn’t around when I was growing up.
My mom didn’t tell him she was pregnant with me.
Said she didn’t trust him enough.
Jeez, she told you that? Must have been hard to hear.
It wasn’t.
My mom is an amazing mother, so it didn’t really matter that my dad wasn’t around
Besides, I trust my mom’s judgment to not tell him.
Wow. Well, I’m sorry to hear that you didn’t have a father in your life.
It’s okay. It’s just part of my story.
I know. But that still had to be rough—growing up without a dad.
Sometimes it was. But everyone deals with things that are hard.
I learned how to adapt to a tough situation very early in life.
I’m luckier than a lot of people.
That’s a good way to look at it.
Man, it’s official—Justin was right.
Haha, what?
He told me that you’re an incredible person.
It’s unbelievable that someone like you even exists.
Well I’m about to blow your mind more…ready?
Ha, absolutely.
I read a Connecticut Yankee in King Arthur’s Court yesterday!
What?!
Yup. I figured I could learn something about you by reading your favorite book.
And??
I loved it.
You were right…it was SO funny.
Yesssss. I’m so glad you liked it.
See? Justin was onto something when he set us up.
I don’t know…I still don’t know what you look like.
Are you saying looks are the only thing that matter to you? 😉
NOOO! But come on, they do matter a bit.
What do you look like?
Idk, I’m average.
Very descriptive.
Hey—I believe you used those words to describe yourself!
Yeah, but then I gave you more details.
True.
I guess I kind of look like Justin, but I’m more muscular.
Uh-oh. I don’t really like super muscular guys, haha
Are you like, body-builder big?
Ha, no. I’m 6’1” and 250lbs.
Tall, dark and handsome. I like it.
I’m a good kisser too.
Griffin! I thought we were taking it slow.
We are. We should.
And Jess, we don’t have to do anything you don’t want to do…
But can we meet?
